{ Introduction  Welcome to this course on the Kalashnikov Sicilian. An enormous amount of work has been put into preparing this course and I am really proud of it, I hope you enjoy the course and also enjoy playing this opening as well!  The Kalashnikov Sicilian is a practical and straightforward opening choice because you can get in your move pretty quickly with ...e5, and straightaway, you are into the variation. The course is well organized to help you tackle the vast amount of information provided within the course.   I recommend you begin with the Quickstarter Guide, which easily provides an overview of the variations in the course, thus providing you with a snippet of the mainlines, some ideas, and explanations on the variations I have picked.Next up, I strongly recommend that you go through the Model Games section, which contains 17 Kalashnikov-themed games that illustrate the Kalashnikov middlegame strategy, they also help to reinforce a lot of the variations which I have recommended in the course, as well as give you an idea on opening strategy and middlegame strategy. The idea is that, once you see a complete game, it helps to put the variations in context and give you a broader understanding of the repertoire.   So, my recommendation for studying this course; Begin with the Quickstarter Guide, then proceed to the  Model Games, and then you can go on with the main course.  Lastly, do not just learn the theory, play the opening, play the opening as quickly as possible, as this will give you a feel for what is important, and can help point out where the gaps in your knowledge are.   It is always best to have a blend of theoretical study and Practice  (playing the opening)  , and you should do just great!  Best of luck,  GM Daniel King. }
