{ A prudent move, exchanging off a pair of pieces and taking the edge off Black's initiative. }
16... Bxc4 17. bxc4 Rxc4
{ Black has won the pawn back and still has the initiative. } 18. Bxa7 Rxc3
{ Threatening ...Qc7, so White retreats the loose bishop. } 19. Be3 Nxe4
{ Black is a pawn up with good central control. Where is White's center now? }
