5... Nf6
{ Simple chess. The knight develops to its best square and attacks the e-pawn. Black is already ahead in the race to develop. }
6. Bd3
{ Any sensible development will give Black a satisfactory game:  6...Bb4+  ,  6...Bc5  ,  6...Be7  ,  6...d6  , but given the opportunity, I believe Black should strike in the middle with the thematic push. }
6... d5 7. exd5 Nxd5
{ I think this is the simplest move, although  7...Qxd5  is possible with the idea of castling queenside. }
8. O-O Ndb4 { Threatens to take the bishop. } 9. Be4 Qxd1 10. Rxd1 Bg4
{ Black is ready to play ...f5. } 11. a3 { If  11.Re1  O-O-O  . } 11... f5
{ That is the little tactic that justifies Black's play. } 12. axb4 fxe4 13. h3
Bxf3 14. gxf3 Bxb4 15. fxe4 Bc5 { The endgame is roughly level. } *

