O-O
{ Black can also play  7...d5  but I like the flexibility of castling. The d-pawn might well advance two squares, but there is also another plan available, namely exchanging on c3, then playing  d6  and exploiting the weak doubled c-pawns. Let's see how White plays then react accordingly. }
