11. Qe1
{ aims to keep Black's king in the centre but the plan can be easily thwarted. }
11... Be6
{ Because Black controls the centre, it is easy to block the e-file. } 12. Bf4
O-O 13. Nd2 Kh8
{ Black would like to play  13...Bd6  , but that would allow  14.Rxe6  . However, after the king's move, the bishop's move is a threat, so the rook has to drop back. }
14. Re2 Bd6
{ In any case, this is a useful exchange for Black, giving the major pieces more freedom. }
15. Bg5 Bxh2+ 16. Kxh2 Ng4+ { wins a pawn. } *

