10. Nc4 { The knight returns to the centre of the board. } 10... Nb4
{ Once White has played the pawn to a4, the b4 square is available for the knight and this is a great position looking at c2 and the important d5 square. The c-file is also cleared for action.   Black can equalise immediately with  10...d5  , but that leads to exchanges and instead, let's keep some juice in the position. }
11. a5 { White secures a square for the knight on b6. } 11... Qc7
