{ Another cool move. White cannot bring the king to safety, so Black can take time to make some solid moves before driving forward.   If  17.O-O  Bxa3  18.Nxa3  Rd2  is better for Black. In which case, what can White do?  On the other hand, Black can improve gradually: ...Nd7, then pawn to ...a6-b5, if possible ...Nc5. It is not easy for White to develop properly without dropping a pawn, and that would spell trouble. }
