14. Be2 Bxc1 15. Rxc1 Ne7
{ Black continues the battle for the d5 square. White cannot keep control. }
16. O-O { would be a strategic mistake: } 16... Bxd5 17. exd5 Qb6
{ Black has the superior pawn structure: the d5 pawn is potentially weak @@StartBracket@@watch out for ...Rc8-c5, or ...Qb6-b7@@EndBracket@@ and the kingside pawn majority, the f and e pawns, are ready to roll down the board. }
