{ Black is getting ready to open the kingside with ...f5, so White should push away the knight. }
16. c3 Nb5
{ This is cannier than exchanging pawns:  16...bxc3  17.bxc3  Nb5  when the knight can be forced back with  18.a4  . With the pawn on b4, playing  17.a4  makes no sense as it can simply be captured en passant. }
