{ This is a great way to open lines and get the queen into the game. } 18. bxa5
Qxa5+ 19. Bd2 Qa7 { So often this is a key diagonal in the Kalashnikov. } 20.
O-O Nd4
{ Black has sacrificed a pawn for tremendous activity. Depending on how White plays, the bishop might well land on g5. Perhaps bishop to d7 @@StartBracket@@or a6@@EndBracket@@ and Rfb8 to press on the a and b files. And, of course, let's not forget the pawn break ...f5, opening up the kingside. }
