{ Blocking the bishop, as well as opening the a7-g1 diagonal, is not good strategy. }
18... Be6 19. f4 { It's not good for the pawn to remain on f3. } 19... exf4 20.
gxf4 { White does best to retain control over the e5 square. } 20... Qd8 21.
Rxa3 Bxd5
{ Getting rid of the knight allows Black's queen to get back into the game. }
22. exd5
{ 22.Qxd5  Qb6+  23.Kh1  Nd4  isn't bad for White, but more accuracy is needed than in the other line. }
22... Qb6+ 23. Rf2 Nd4
{ Black has decent counterplay with the rooks coming to c8 and e8. They will be far better placed than White's split rooks. The computer believes that the position is equal, and we must bow to its superior knowledge, but thankfully chess is still played between humans and I would back Black. }
